dc_title_s: Mako, Formosa (Taiwan), Boko-cho, Mako-Shicho. A.M.S. L991
dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 23.566667. South Decimal Degree 23.550000. East Decimal Degree 119.583333. West Decimal Degree 119.550000. Alternate title: Mako. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:8,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by form lines and hachures. Compiled in 1945 form aerial photography dated July 1943 and July 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:25,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2017-IV SW, 1944; and Japanese Hydrographic Chart No. 235, 1932. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Ma-kung [Makung].
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
